<ServicePage
  name="Tree Trimming & Pruning"
  slug="tree-trimming"
  headline="Tree Trimming & Pruning in Concord, NC"
  intro="Expert pruning to keep your trees healthy, safe, and looking their best. Residential and commercial properties across Cabarrus County."
  priceRange="$150 – $1,200"
  benefits={[
    'ISA pruning standards',
    'Improves tree health & appearance',
    'Prevents storm damage',
    'Clears power lines & structures',
    'Free estimates',
    'Licensed & insured',
  ]}
  body={`
    <h2>Keep Your Trees Healthy & Safe</h2>
    <p>Regular trimming isn't just cosmetic — it's essential for tree health, structural integrity, and property safety. Overgrown branches can damage roofs, block sightlines, interfere with power lines, and create hazards during storms. Professional pruning removes these risks while promoting healthy growth.</p>

    <h2>Types of Tree Trimming We Offer</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Crown thinning:</strong> Selective branch removal to improve light and air circulation</li>
      <li><strong>Crown raising:</strong> Removing lower branches for clearance over driveways, walkways, and structures</li>
      <li><strong>Crown reduction:</strong> Reducing overall size while maintaining the tree's natural shape</li>
      <li><strong>Deadwood removal:</strong> Eliminating dead or dying branches to prevent falling hazards</li>
      <li><strong>Vista pruning:</strong> Strategic trimming to open up views while preserving tree health</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>When to Trim Your Trees</h2>
    <p>Most trees benefit from pruning during their dormant season (late fall through early spring), but dead or hazardous branches should be removed immediately regardless of season. We recommend annual inspections for large trees near structures.</p>

    <h2>Tree Trimming Costs in Concord</h2>
    <p>Trimming costs depend on tree size, number of trees, accessibility, and the extent of work needed. Most residential trimming jobs fall between $150 and $1,200. Multi-tree discounts are available.</p>
  `}
